item.title: Kamala Harris, Donald Trump share 'awkward' handshake
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump shook hands during their first face-to-face meeting at Tuesday night's presidential debate. They debated key issues like immigration and abortion in an intense encounter without a live audience. This debate provided a critical opportunity to influence undecided voters ahead of the November election.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Trump should not be telling a woman what to do with her body': Kamala Harris
item.description: Kamala Harris criticized Donald Trump's stance on abortion rights during a debate, emphasizing her support for reinstating Roe v. Wade. She condemned Trump-backed abortion bans in over 20 states as draconian and immoral. Trump defended state-level regulation and emphasized his support for In vitro fertilisation (IVF). The debate underscores the high stakes of the upcoming election.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US presidential debate: Kamala, Trump on policy, international affairs, high price and illegal immigrations -Key takeaways
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump faced off in their first debate. Harris highlighted her plans for an 'opportunity economy' and criticized Trump's policies. Trump responded by clarifying his tariff strategy, asserting that it would bring financial benefits to the US.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Georgia school shooting: Suspect's mom's call wasn't the only alert, multiple warnings overlooked before Apalachee high attack
item.description: The recent school shooting at Apalachee High School in Georgia has revealed multiple missed warnings leading up to the tragedy. An urgent call from the shooter's mother and an anonymous tip about planned attacks were not acted upon promptly. The incident resulted in four deaths and nine injuries, raising serious questions about school safety protocols.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Abortion-rights measure will appear in ballot,' Missouri's Supreme Court rules
item.description: Missouri's Supreme Court has ruled that a proposed amendment to restore abortion rights will be included on the November ballot. This decision enables voters to decide on legal abortion for the first time since Roe v. Wade was overturned. The measure needs at least 50% voter support, with recent polls showing 52% in favor.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'America is going bankrupt extremely quickly,' Elon Musk warns as debt continues to accelerate
item.description: Elon Musk has warned that the United States is rapidly approaching bankruptcy with a national debt over $35 trillion. Speaking at the All-In Summit 2024, he highlighted the need for deregulation and smaller government. Musk pointed out that interest payments on this debt have now exceeded $1 trillion annually, stressing future generations will bear this burden.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Joe Biden sparks social media frenzy with 'Tomorrow I’m doing 9/11' comment, watch video
item.description: US President Joe Biden's comment about "doing 9/11" has caused a social media uproar. During a discussion, he mentioned he would be commemorating the September 11 attacks, which many found poorly phrased. He clarified that he would visit key memorials in New York and Pennsylvania to honor the victims of the terrorist attacks.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Democrat Eric Swalwell slams viral Trump cat and duck memes: 'What in the hell is this?'
item.description: Rep. Eric Swalwell's reaction to viral memes featuring Donald Trump with cats and ducks has gone viral. The memes originated from a debunked conspiracy theory alleging Haitian immigrants were abducting pets in Ohio. Swalwell criticized Republican House Judiciary Chairman Jim Jordan for promoting these unfounded claims on social media.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump vs Harris: Betting markets reveal who’s expected to win the US presidential debate
item.description: Anticipation for the first presidential debate between Donald Trump and Kamala Harris is high, with betting markets favoring Harris to win the debate. However, Trump remains favored to win the overall election. Experts suggest debates may not drastically sway election outcomes unless they are particularly one-sided, highlighting an interesting dynamic in this political contest.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris' throwback video with Willie Brown viral: 'Are you his daughter?'
item.description: The viral footage was from 1995 where the subject was Willie Brown described as a man "notorious for his flamboyant lifestyle, flashy clothes, fancy parties and fine women and fast cars". Kamala Harris was seen in the video replying "No, I am not" to one asking "Are you his daughter?"
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: When dean of Barron Trump's new school called Donald 'threat'
item.description: Barron Trump, son of former President Donald Trump, has enrolled at NYU's Stern School of Business. Interim dean JP Eggers, who once criticized Trump's presidency in a 2020 letter, met Barron on his first day. Barron's choice of university was widely speculated and he ultimately chose NYU for its proximity to their Manhattan home and also because he liked the college.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Have Donald Trump and Kamala Harris ever met? 'I have a photo of her...'
item.description: Kamala Harris' ex-boyfriend Willie Brown claimed to have introduced (not face to face) Kamala Harris to then businessman Donald Trump. Brown, Harris and a few other associates had been in Cambridge, Massachusetts, where Brown was speaking at Harvard, when Trump sent up his plane to ferry the group to Teterboro, New Jersey. Trump urgently wanted Brown’s advice on how to build a property in Los Angeles​.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Two Delta planes collide at Atlanta airport, wing knocks off tail
item.description: Two Delta planes collided while they were taxiing at Atlanta International Airport on Tuesday leading to no injuries. The wing of one plane knocked off the tail of the other and the passengers were accommodated on alternative flights. The Federal Aviation Administration said Delta Flight 295's wingtip struck the tail of Endeavor Air Flight 5526.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: UK says started 'termination of all direct air services' to Iran
item.description: The UK said Tuesday it has started terminating "all direct air services between the UK and Iran" as part of new sanctions on Tehran for supplying Russia with missiles to use in Ukraine. "(This) is why we have begun the termination of all direct air services between the UK and Iran."

item.title: Last-minute changes in Kamala Harris' debate script: What happened at Pittsburgh hotel
item.description: ​Kamala Harris camped at a Pittsburgh hotel for five days preparing for the debate tonight in which she will face Donald Trump for the first time for the presidential duel. Inside the hotel, reports said, there were highly choreographed debate practice sessions including a stage, a replica TV lighting, and Philippe Reines acting as Donald Trump in mock debates.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: China refuses to sign agreement to ban AI from controlling nuclear weapons
item.description: China opted out of the 'Blueprint for Action' agreement aimed at banning AI from controlling nuclear weapons. The non-binding agreement was adopted at the REAIM summit in Seoul with over 100 countries present. It stresses human control over nuclear actions and acknowledges the need for further discussions on military AI policies. Russia was excluded due to its Ukraine invasion.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: JD Vance was 'caught' spreading rumors about Haitian immigrants. He doesn't care
item.description: A day after JD Vance was caught furthering a racist conspiracy theory that Haitian immigrants settled in Ohio's Springfield are eating pet cats and ducks, Vance said his office received many calls from Springfield residents who complained that the pets of their neighbors were stolen by Haitian migrants. Vance said even if these are rumors and may turn out to be false, the migrant problem in Ohio is real.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Melania Trump drops strategic video ahead of debate: 'Attempt to end my husband's life...'
item.description: Melania Trump released a video seeking answers for the assassination attempt on Donald Trump. Though it was a promotion for her upcoming memoir, the video came hours before the ABC News debate between Donald Trump and Kamala Harris. Melania has been promoting her memoir -- to be released on October 8 -- on her social media accounts. The memoir is about her but the promotional material she chose so far are all about her husband Donald Trump.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Demented': Donald Trump facing questions about age, capacity in debate with Harris
item.description: As Donald Trump and Kamala Harris take to the ABC News debate stage tonight, it will be 78-year-old Donald Trump facing the question of age and senility against Kamala Harris -- 20 years younger than him. Donald Trump's recent statement on childcare that 'childcare is childcare' raised questions over his rambling though Trump campaign asserted that Trump has more energy and stamina than anyone in politics.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
